# ============================================
# phiUture — environment variables
# ============================================
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in values.
#
# NOTE: none of these are VITE_-prefixed, so they are SERVER-only and never
# bundled into or visible from the browser. They are read by the content proxy
# (api/content/[file].js), not by client code. Set them on the host (e.g. the
# Vercel project → Environment Variables), then redeploy.

# Live content updates without a redeploy.
# --------------------------------------------
# Editable content lives in JSON files under src/data/ (products.json,
# beyond.json, about.json). In production the site fetches the newest committed
# version at runtime through a same-origin proxy, so editing a file at the
# source and committing updates the live site within a minute — no rebuild.
#
# Point GITHUB_DATA_BASE at the RAW URL of that folder:
#   https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<user>/<repo>/<branch>/src/data
#
# Example:
#   GITHUB_DATA_BASE="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thebitanpaul/phiUture/main/src/data"
#
# Leave unset to run purely on the bundled JSON (updates require a redeploy).
# GITHUB_DATA_BASE=""

# Optional — only if the content source becomes PRIVATE. A bearer token the
# proxy sends to the upstream; stays on the server, never reaches the client.
# GITHUB_DATA_TOKEN=""
